# git-mailmap(5) — canonicalise historical author identities.
#
# Format: <canonical-email> <commit-email>  (name-only forms also supported)
#
# The maintainer's ``~/.gitconfig`` used to carry a work email
# (mehmet.fahri@mayadem.com). That email stamped most of main's
# early history. ``mehmetfahriozmen@gmail.com`` is the canonical
# identity for this open-source project going forward.
#
# Mailmap is a read-time display rewrite — ``git log``,
# ``git shortlog``, and GitHub's commit-list UI all apply it, but
# the commit SHAs themselves are not changed. Chose this over a
# ``git filter-repo`` rewrite because the non-destructive path is
# honest ("here's who this was, here's how to reach them now") and
# has zero blast radius for clones, forks, and open PRs. See
# docs/PLAN.md for the decision context.
#
# The GitHub-noreply identity (39158545+mfozmen@users.noreply.github.com)
# appears on squash-merge commits and is intentionally left alone —
# it's how GitHub identifies the user on their platform and keeping
# it preserves the signal "this came in via a GitHub merge UI".

Mehmet Fahri Özmen <mehmetfahriozmen@gmail.com> <mehmet.fahri@mayadem.com>
